{
  "texts": [
    "One of the derivatives of NI is the phenomenon of Agency, which reductively means the ability of the person to choose and act autonomously based on world modeling, planning and incentives.",
    "Giddens theorized the concept of structuration, which states that there is a constant actively dynamic interrelation among agents, as the choice makers, and structure in lieu of the chances they may perform.",
    "He famously introduced humans as \"knowledgeable agents\" with the capacity to understand the circumstances and consequences of their actions, thus they can possibly exercise choice [2][3][4][5].",
    "By other accounts, agency, at least as it is broadly understood, requires that there be some kind of animating \"intention\" behind the observed action.",
    "For example, when I observe a painter painting, I attribute intention to the movement of his hands and the shift in his gaze, but not to his breathing."
  ]
}